The Principal Members of the US Intelligence Community are the heads of the 17 agencies that make up the US Intelligence Community. The Principal Members meet periodically to coordinate and share information.
In 1985, the Principal Members of the US Intelligence Community included:
1. Director of Central Intelligence (DCI) - William J. Casey
2. Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) - William H. Webster
3. Director of the National Security Agency (NSA) - Lieutenant General William E. Odom
4. Director of the Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA) - General David C. Jones
5. Director of the National Reconnaissance Office (NRO) - Benjamin G. Black, Jr.
6. Director of the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) - Rear Admiral Robert D. Murrett
7. Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) - William J. Casey (from 1981)
8. Director of the National Security Council (NSC) - William P. Clark, Jr.
9. Attorney General of the United States - Edwin Meese
10. Secretary of Defense - Caspar W. Weinberger
11. Secretary of Energy - Donald H. Rumsfeld
12. Secretary of State - George P. Shultz
13. Secretary of the Treasury - James A. Baker III
14. Director of the National Security Agency (NSA) - Lieutenant General William E. Odom
15. Director of the Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA) - General David C. Jones
16. Director of the National Reconnaissance Office (NRO) - Benjamin G. Black, Jr.
17. Director of the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) - Rear Admiral Robert D. Murrett
Please note that the list of Principal Members of the US Intelligence Community may have changed over time, and the information provided here is accurate as of 1985.
